docs.abstract: In an appearance at the Economic Club of New York, the president overstated some of the economy’s gains on his watch, understated others and often cited inaccurate statistics.
docs.snippet: In an appearance at the Economic Club of New York, the president overstated some of the economy’s gains on his watch, understated others and often cited inaccurate statistics.
docs.lead_paragraph: The United States economy is slowing and wage growth has slipped, but household incomes are rising and the unemployment rate is at a half-century low. This is the complicated — and somewhat contradictory — state of the American economy that President Trump painted over with a big smiley face at the Economic Club of New York on Tuesday.

headline.main: Fact Check: Trump’s Claims on the Economy

docs.abstract: The form opens the door to student aid. But it’s “a terrible measure of what people can actually afford,” one expert said. And many families will be asked to pay more, anyway.
docs.snippet: The form opens the door to student aid. But it’s “a terrible measure of what people can actually afford,” one expert said. And many families will be asked to pay more, anyway.
docs.lead_paragraph: Like millions of other parents, Julie Phipps filled out the federal form last November that determined her college-bound daughter was eligible for financial aid. She also learned how much the federal government figured her family could contribute to the bill: $14,000.

headline.main: FAFSA Says How Much You Can Pay for College. It’s Often Wrong.
headline.print_headline: Key to Aid For College Can Jolt, Too

docs.abstract: The beleaguered office space company is said to be planning to cut its work force by at least a third in a bid to stabilize its business.
docs.snippet: The beleaguered office space company is said to be planning to cut its work force by at least a third in a bid to stabilize its business.
docs.lead_paragraph: WeWork is preparing to cut at least 4,000 people from its work force as it tries to stabilize itself after the company’s breakneck growth racked up heavy losses and led it to the brink of collapse, two people with knowledge of the matter said.

headline.print_headline: Big Layoffs Set to Begin At WeWork

docs.abstract: “None of this had to happen”: The network’s new sexual harassment policy did not prevent them from leaving after accusations against the star’s husband, a producer.
docs.snippet: “None of this had to happen”: The network’s new sexual harassment policy did not prevent them from leaving after accusations against the star’s husband, a producer.
docs.lead_paragraph: In May, CBS employees received an email introducing a new plan for handling sexual harassment complaints. There would be a “very expanded and visible” structure, the email said, with “highly trained HR executives” at every CBS program to “ensure safety and build trust."

headline.main: Two Female Writers Quit Patricia Heaton’s CBS Show After Making Complaints
